   version stable 0.63.0
   require init-functions libtool shadow
  optional Linux-PAM  '' --without-authpam   for pluggable authentication
  optional db         '' ''                  for db based authnetication
  optional gdbm       '' ''                  for gdbm based authnetication
  optional mysql      '' --without-authmysql for mysql based authentication
  optional openldap   '' --without-authldap  for ldap features
  optional postgresql '' --without-authpgsql for postgresql based authentication
  category network/email
 attribute library makej multilib-dual
    source $SOURCEFORGE_URL courier/authlib/$VERSION/courier-authlib-$VERSION.tar.bz2
      info home  http://www.courier-mta.org/
  estimate 3000
      desc 'courier authnetication library
The Courier Authentication Library is a generic authentication API
that encapsulates the process of validating account passwords.
In addition to reading the traditional account passwords from
/etc/passwd, the account information can alternatively be
obtained from an LDAP, MySQL, PostgreSQL, GDBM or a DB file.
The Courier authentication library must be installed before building
any Courier  packages that needs direct access to mailboxes (in other
words, all packages except for courier-sox and courier-analog).'
